inject deprecation warnings into HTTP responses via the Warning header\n\n5. **Metrics Tracking** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go):\n   - Tracks deprecated API requests through metrics (requested_deprecated_apis gauge)\n   - Adds audit annotations to flag deprecated API usage\n   - Instruments route functions with deprecated flag and removal release information\n\n6. **API Installation Flow** (pkg/controlplane/apiserver/apis.go):\n   - During API server startup, `InstallAPIs()` creates a ResourceExpirationEvaluator based on the current Kubernetes version\n   - Calls `RemoveDeletedKinds()` before installing any API groups to filter out removed APIs\n   - Only installs API groups and versions that should be served in the current Kubernetes version\n\n7. **Route Installation** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go):\n   - For each API resource, checks if it's deprecated using `IsDeprecated()` \n   - Extracts the removal release using `RemovedRelease()`\n   - Generates warning messages using `WarningMessage()`\n   - Wraps all route handlers with `AddWarningsHandler()` to inject warnings into responses\n   - Passes deprecation and removal information to `InstrumentRouteFunc()` for metrics tracking\n\nThe enforcement chain ensures that:\n- APIs with removal dates in the past are not served at all\n- APIs currently marked as deprecated generate warnings in all responses\n- Clients are informed about which versions will be unavailable and what replacements to use\n- Metrics and audit logs track deprecated API usage for cluster administrators to monitor migration progress"
